modules.description: This implementation facilitates **public key-based user authentication** through **registration and challenge-response protocols**, supporting **FIDO-U2F hardware tokens** and **"none" attestation** with **P256 elliptic curve keys**. It processes **cryptographic challenges**, **attestation responses**, **X.509 certificates**, and **transport metadata** to enable secure authentication workflows, requiring external storage for credential IDs and public keys. Typical applications include **passwordless login systems** using hardware security keys (e.g., YubiKey) or platform-trusted modules (TPM), where servers verify client-held private keys via signed challenges.
